Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. In a large #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @mushroom stock concentrate{3} and @water{4%cups}; microwave until hot, ~{3-5%minutes}. Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick @sage{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; thinly slice leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add garlic and shallot. Cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @Arborio rice{¾%cup}; stir until translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add ½ cup stock; stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining stock—adding ½ cup at a time and stirring until liquid has mostly absorbed—until rice is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

While risotto cooks, toss @butternut squash{8%ounce}(peeled and diced) on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @scallops{8%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a second large pan over medium-high heat. Add scallops and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat. Remove scallops from pan and set aside, covered. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for scallops over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until butter is foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in sage leaves and a squeeze of lemon juice. Turn off heat; carefully transfer to a #small bowl{}. Once risotto is done, stir in roasted squash, lemon zest, @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, @butter{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Taste and season risotto with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice if desired. Divide between bowls and top with scallops. Drizzle with brown butter. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> What a powerhouse: every element of this recipe goes above and beyond in fitting in as much lush, decadent flavor as can be contained on a plate.